---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection';
---

<BaseLayout title="Dryer Vent Cleaning in Stanton, CA | Hilo Heating and Air" description="Professional dryer vent cleaning services in Stanton, CA and surrounding Orange County areas. Prevent fires and improve dryer efficiency.">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue to-blue-800 py-20 sm:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Dryer Vent Cleaning in Stanton, CA</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">Clothes coming out of the dryer still damp? Most of the time it's a clogged vent, not a tired dryer. HiLo Heating and Air does dryer vent cleaning for homes around Stanton and Orange County.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">Why Dryer Vent Cleaning Matters More Than You Think</h2>

        <p>Clothes coming out of the dryer still damp? You run a second cycle and figure that's just how the machine is now. Probably not. Most of the time it's a clogged vent, not a tired dryer. HiLo Heating and Air does <strong>dryer vent cleaning</strong> for homes around Stanton, CA and the rest of Orange County, and it's a small job that prevents some pretty serious problems.</p>

        <h2>Why This Isn't Just a Minor Thing</h2>
        <p>Lint builds up inside the vent line no matter how religiously you clean the lint trap. The trap catches some of it, sure, but a lot makes it past and starts collecting further down the line. Months go by, then years, and eventually you've got a real blockage on your hands. Longer runs, sharp bends, vents that go up through the roof instead of out a side wall — those clog faster than a simple straight shot.</p>
        <p>This isn't just annoying. Clogged dryer vents are one of the more common causes of house fires, full stop. <strong>Dryer vent cleaning</strong> isn't something to keep putting off, even if your dryer's still technically running fine.</p>

        <h2>How Do You Know It's Time?</h2>
        <p>A few warning signs tend to show up first. Clothes needing two or three cycles to actually dry. The dryer feeling hot on the outside when you touch it. A burning smell during a cycle. More lint than usual collecting around the door. One of these on its own, worth checking out. A couple together, you're probably overdue.</p>

        <h2>What We Actually Do</h2>
        <p>Our techs handle vent lines of any length, including roof exits and runs with multiple bends — the tricky ones other companies sometimes skip. We use real tools to pull lint out from deep inside the line, not just whatever a shop vac can reach near the opening. Once that's clear, we check the vent cap and exit point outside, since people forget that part gets blocked too.</p>
        <p>We'll also glance at the connection between the dryer and the vent itself. Loose or damaged spots there can leak even after everything else is cleaned out. Every <strong>dryer vent cleaning</strong> job ends with a quick test run, so you can actually feel the airflow difference before we leave.</p>

        <h2>Why Bother</h2>
        <p>Past the fire risk — which honestly should be reason enough — regular <strong>dryer vent cleaning</strong> means shorter drying cycles, lower energy bills, and less strain on a machine that's not fighting blocked airflow anymore. Laundry day gets a lot less annoying.</p>
        <p>HiLo Heating and Air clears the whole line, not just the easy part. Pricing's straightforward, and if something past the vent itself needs attention, we'll tell you instead of pretending everything's fine.</p>

        <h2>Get It Scheduled</h2>
        <p>Don't wait for a burning smell before taking this seriously. Call HiLo Heating and Air to get your <strong>dryer vent cleaning</strong> on the books, and let your dryer actually do its job again.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How often should this be done?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Once a year for most homes. Longer or more complicated vent runs might need it more.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How do I know my vent's clogged?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Slow-drying clothes, a hot dryer exterior, burning smells, extra lint around the door — any of those is a sign.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">My dryer still works fine, so do I really need this?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes. A working dryer with a clogged vent is still a fire hazard, even without obvious performance issues yet.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How long does the job take?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Usually under an hour, depending on how long and complex your vent line is.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Can a clogged vent actually hurt my dryer?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yeah — restricted airflow makes it work harder, which wears it out faster and means more repairs over time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Do you handle roof-exit vents?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">We do, plus runs with multiple bends or awkward layouts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Will this lower my energy bill?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Often, since a clear vent lets the dryer finish cycles faster without fighting blocked airflow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Do you check the outside vent cap too?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes — the whole line gets checked, not just the part near the machine.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Is the work guaranteed?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes, backed by our standard workmanship guarantee.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How do I book this?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Call (714) 853-5534 or email info@hiloheatingandair.com and we'll set something up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-brand-blue/5 py-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-brand-blue font-semibold">HiLo Heating and Air · 8131 Electric Ave, Stanton, CA 90680, United States</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1"><a href="tel:+17148535534" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">(714) 853-5534</a> · <a href="mailto:info@hiloheatingandair.com" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">info@hiloheatingandair.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection client:visible />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
